           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white">
                      <font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> As a 57 Necro, went on my first raid on Plane of Hate this weekend and thought I'd share some of the experience.<br /><br />I did my homework by downloading maps, reading Hate guides, etc..  Learned about the zone-in, safe spots, etc..<br /><br />I arrived late for the raid (about 15 50+ peeps).  We only had one Wizzy, so I asked a friend (62 Wiz) for a port up.  He informed me that we would both die in the attempt.  Turned out he was correct, but the raid group dragged us to camp and rezzed us.  Cool, I'm in.<br /><br />We spent the day pulling Hate yard trash.  Clerics of Innouruuk, rats, gargoyles, Lichs.  My biggest problem was that most of these mobs are highly poison/disease resistant so EBolt, CoC, Torbas all commonly resisted.  Had to switch to Ignite Blood, Vex, even Eternities Torment (lots of undead).  This was my first big experience with the stupidity of Scent of Terris (if it lands I lower resistance, but it NEVER landed).<br /><br />Clerics were the most fun because of the self-heals.  Get them below 20% and next they are at 80%.  I think one of them got this off 4 times.<br />Fortunately we had two great enchanters that controlled the adds and kept Clerics from healing each other.<br /><br />Over a period of 8 hours, I was asked for two twitches from the main cleric, other than that they wanted my damage.  Half way through the raid I changed groups and the new group's comment was "Now WE are the XP group'.  This turned out to be very true, only time we didn't take the XP was after I was lom from twitching the Cleric.<br /><br />Really missed having Jabober with me but that would have been way too high a risk in Hate.<br /><br />At the end we decided to pull the Maestro.  My eyes were lighting up with visions of moving my epic forward.  Unfortunately, it was a total wipe.  I never saw his HP drop and he just dropped person after person.  I feigned, but his AE spells brought me up for the eventual kill.  Anyone know the strategy for taking him down?<br /><br />I did get a few Blue Diamonds, and a Wand of Souls.  And a new appreciation for Hate and the two guilds that worked so well together, Gift of Divinity and Seventh Sphere.<br /><br />I realize this is a real n00b post, but it was new and exciting for me and should be nastalgic for a lot of you.<br /><br />Waldina<br />Cazic-Thule Necromancer</span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
