                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Maestro cast/proc's an AE lifetap...so you usually don't wanna 'pull' him, but rather fight him in his lair (usually near the throne).  The key is to have your aggro/melee be the only folks that are taking the AE, usually by pinning Maestro in a corner, and having all your casters remain standing and out of AE range.  Since it's a lifetap, the more folks Maestro hits with it, the more HP he regains...so it really pays to pull the casters back and let the tanks keep him in a corner.  Once he's not recharging himself on your entire raids lifeforce, he's really quite easy to deal with from a melee perspective.  <br /><br />Basically, have the casters avoid aggro and his AE, and you should be golden.  If he starts ping ponging around in your caster area, you're in for a world of hurt.<br /><br />Good travels,<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=283327" target="_blank">Thrull</a><br />Emerald Templars<br />Quellious</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
