                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I always loved Hate ... I would forget DoTs next time and nuke like a wizard. Get a mage damage bracer if you can, load up Deflux (if you have it) and your undead nuke, run Lich/whatever and nuke till your heart's content. Get a speed ring also, and you can really overkill on undead mobs too, since the DD is hell cheap. PoK Venom might be useful on living mobs too, and consider having a heal memmed just in case, and maybe ST. I've managed to do a lot on lil raids sometimes by taking over mezzing after the chanters died, or healing when all the healers were OOM.<br /><br />With pets ... sometimes they are OK, like the first "safe corner" as we call it on Rodcet, and the second floor is semi OK. The really buggy pathing I found is the Maestro's hall ... where you can have a pet running around in circles unable to touch a mob a few feet away. before Summon Companion, this was a total pain in the ass. Keep it memmed if you are using a pet, sure, Boneboy might not aggro and trainbring anymore, but he sure can get lost somewhere easy enough still.<br /><br />Saminga Amaranth, 60th Druidclubber of Avatars of Discord, Spankmistress of Rodcet Nife.<br /><br />"If <i>I</i> go back home now, I'll be clubbing druids." Lias, <i>Soul Music</i>, Terry Pratchett.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
